        "eyebrow": "Our Story",
        "heading": "A Garage, a CAD Seat, and a Problem to Solve",
        "paragraph": "<p>KingWorX was born out of frustration. Our founder — a passionate car enthusiast and mechanical engineer — spent years watching Australian car builders pay premium prices for parts that were mediocre in fitment, finish, and function. The industry gap was obvious: no one was designing parts <em>specifically</em> for the cars Australians actually drive.</p><p>So we sat down at a CAD workstation, modelled our first underbody component from scratch, and had it manufactured to tight tolerances. The result? Parts that actually fit. Every time.</p>",
